: SHOULD BE UNCOMMENTED ONLY IF THE DATA BEING TRANSMITTED IS EBCDIC
: DATA.  THE PATCH WILL TRANSLATE FROM EBCDIC TO ASCII PRIOR TO DISPLAYING
: THE INTERPRETATION.  IF THE DATA IS ALREADY IN ASCII, THIS WILL PROVIDE
: AN INCORRECT TRANSLATION.  THE CODE THAT IS COMMENTED OUT IS AT SYMBOL
: XDRISH.
